
[1]unfaithfulness

   UNFA'ITHFULNESS, n. Neglect or violation of vows, promises, allegiance
   or other duty; breach of confidence or trust reposed; perfidiousness;
   treachery; as the unfaithfulness of a subject to his prince or the
   state; the unfaithfulness of a husband to his wife, or of a wife to her
   husband; the unfaithfulness of an agent, servant or officer.
